  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Workplace Safety & Health Officer (WSHO)",
  "description": "<h3>Job Description</h3><p>We are looking for a <strong>qualified Workplace Safety & Health Officer (WSHO)</strong> to join our team on a <strong>short-term contract</strong> for an ongoing project.</p><h3>Responsibilities</h3><ul><li><p>Ensure compliance with Workplace Safety & Health (WSH) regulations</p></li><li><p>Conduct site inspections and risk assessments</p></li><li><p>Prepare and maintain WSH-related documentation and reports</p></li><li><p>Conduct toolbox meetings and safety briefings</p></li><li><p>Liaise with relevant authorities, consultants, and site teams</p></li><li><p>Investigate incidents and recommend corrective actions</p></li></ul><h3>Requirements</h3><ul><li><p>Registered <strong>WSHO</strong> with MOM (Singapore)</p></li><li><p>Relevant WSH qualifications and certifications</p></li><li><p>Prior experience in construction / industrial environment preferred</p></li><li><p>Able to start work on short notice is an advantage</p></li><li><p>Strong communication and reporting skills</p></li></ul><h3>Contract Details</h3><ul><li><p><strong>Duration:</strong> 3 to 8 months</p></li><li><p><strong>Working Arrangement:</strong> Contract / Project-based</p></li><li><p><strong>Salary:</strong> Negotiable (based on experience)</p></li></ul>",
